Wash and dry produce.

Dice @tomato{1}(diced). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Trim and halve @jalapeño{1} lengthwise, removing ribs and seeds for less heat; mince. Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1} into strips.

In a small #pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3⁄4 cup water (1 1⁄2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil; cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, minced onion, a squeeze of lime juice, and as much jalapeño as you like. Season with salt and pepper.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lime juice, and a pinch of @chili powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later). Season with salt and pepper. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add sliced onion and green pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{7-9%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Lower heat and add a splash of water if veggies begin to brown too quickly.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{} and cover to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%ounce}, @southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, and remaining chili powder. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> Ground Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and a splash of water; cook until saucy, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between bowls and top with turkey and veggies. Drizzle with crema. Top with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup} and pico de gallo. Serve with @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce} and remaining lime wedges on the side.